<HEADLINE> Zambia Committed to Enabling Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government will
continue its economic recovery program and the creation of an
enabling political environment for the country's development.
</P>
<P>
This was reiterated here today by finance minister Ronald
Penza while signing a five-year-development cooperation package
with the European Union amounting to 248 billion Kwacha (190
million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Penza noted that the existence of a stable macro-economic
environment is imperative for a country to achieve sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
The funding from the European Union will be channeled into
various areas of development in Zambia, according to the
minister. 
</P>
