<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ICRC to Establish Office in Tirana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The International Committee of the
Red Cross (ICRC) is setting up an office in Tirana this week while
the unrest in Albania is continuing to spread, according to a
press release issued here today by the ICRC.
</P>
<P>
Since returning to Albania on March 4, eight ICRC delegates,
who are staying in a hotel in central Tirana before their office
is established, have been conducting surveys in the south and
meeting the highest Albanian authorities in the capital to seek
permission to meet detainees held by the government, the ICRC
said.
</P>
<P>
On the current situation in Albania, the ICRC said, "Insurgents
have seized control of a quarter of the national territory. In the
south of the country, law and order are no longer enforced and
military bases have been abandoned to the population. As a result,
large numbers of people are armed."
</P>
<P>
Quoting unofficial sources, the ICRC said, "At least 40 have
died since the beginning of the insurrection."
</P>
<P>
The ICRC said that the Albanian Red Cross is delivering medical
aid and food to hospitals throughout the country, including the
areas of unrest. To date, the ICRC has provided it with essential
surgical supplies for the treatment of 400 wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
