<HEADLINE> Angolan Plane Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The national radio said today an
Antonov-12 plane crashed over Lucapa city in the northeastern
Lunda-Norte Province on Wednesday morning, killing 16 people.
</P>
<P>
The ex-Soviet made plane crashed 150 meters from the runway of
the Lucapa airport, killing all those on board, including four
Russian crew, Director of the National Aviation Airline Branco
Ferreira was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the reason for the crash was not known, but poor
visuality because of fog when the plane landed might cause
misconduct. 
