<HEADLINE> Swedish Economy Edges Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 13 (Xinhua)-- The Swedish economy grew 1.1
percent in 1996, the weakest year since 1993, according to
Statistics of Sweden today.
</P>
<P>
Consumption rose by 1.5 percent last year, largely due to a
rise of 18 percent in car sales while food sales increased 3.1
percent, but the saving quota fell 5.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although last year's economy downed against the 3.2 percent
growth 1995, it remained higher than the average forecast of 0.9
percent. 
</P>
