<HEADLINE> French State Secretary for Health to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- French State Secretary for Health
Herve Gaymard will begin a three-day visit to China next Thursday
to sign an agreement of cooperation in the field of public health
and medicine with Chinese Health Minister Chen Minzhang, said the
French Health Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
Gaymard will attend seminars of the Third France-China
Pharmaceutical Day to be held in Shanghai on March 19 to 21, which
is organized by the National Syndicate of Pharmaceutical Industry
of France and the French Agency of Medicine.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 Chinese and French pharmaceutical industrialists,
doctors, hospital directors and pharmacists, including 150
representatives from 29 French pharmaceutical laboratories, will
attend the France-China Pharmaceutical Day, the third of its kind
to be held in China.
</P>
<P>
Those attending the seminars will discuss the new progress of
medical science, health security, problems faced by pharmaceutical
industry and regulation of health spendings.
</P>
<P>
Gaymard will attend the signing of an agreement between the
Chinese city of Tianjin and the French pharmaceutical company
Beaufour-Ipsen on the creation of a pharmaceutical joint venture
in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
He will also inaugurate in Shanghai a factory of the Ethypharm
Laboratory of France, and visit Shanghai University II and Ruijin
Hospital of Shanghai. 
</P>
