-- Congress bent to pressure not to rebuke Mexico over the drug
trade and struggled to find a gentler way to complain without
harming Mexico's economy.
</P>
<P>
A bill under consideration in the House would revoke President
Clinton's certification of Mexico as fully cooperating in fighting
drug trafficking. But the White House threatened a veto, even
though the bill would allow Clinton to waive the legal effects of
the declaration.
</P>
<P>
