resolution to require the White House to submit a second budget
for the coming year. Congressional analysts have described the
first one as flawed by overly optimistic assumptions about the
economy. The White House said it had no intention of offering a
new budget and called on the Republicans to propose their own
alternative.
</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
