Treaty Organization, the Clinton administration is planning an
all-out selling effort to convince Congress and the American
people of the wisdom of extending formal security guarantees to
former Soviet bloc countries.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Embassies in Albania ordered their citizens to leave as
instability spread and mobs angered by pyramid-scheme losses armed
themselves with looted army weapons. The United States told 160
employees and dependents, as well as 2,000 other Americans, to
book flights. 
