<HEADLINE> Situation Further Worsens in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Gunfire roared throughout the
Albanian capital of Tirana overnight, though President Sali
Berisha announced that a new government for ethnic reconciliation
was established last night.
</P>
<P>
The new government was sworn in this morning, but there was a
panic run on bread among local people who defied intensified
gunfire.
</P>
<P>
Banks and most shops were closed today in fear of lootings and
the international airport in Tirana was closed down.
</P>
<P>
Tirana Mayor Albert Brojka today appealed once again to all
Albanians to keep calm to avoid casualties.
</P>
<P>
Armed rioters Wednesday looted and burned the Tirana Military
Academy and military depots in the suburbs of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The unrests, which started in southern Albania last month and
escalated into armed turmoil, have spread across the Balkan
country.
</P>
<P>
The riots were sparked by the collapse of government investment
schemes which made almost all Albanian families lose money.
</P>
