<HEADLINE> ICRC Establishing Office in Tirana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The International Committee of the
Red Cross (ICRC) is setting up an office in Tirana this week while
the unrest in Albania is continuing to spread, according to a
press release issued here today by the ICRC.
</P>
<P>
Since their return to Albania on March 4, eight ICRC delegates,
who are staying in a hotel in central Tirana before their office
is established, have been conducting surveys in the south and
meeting the highest Albanian authorities in the capital, the ICRC
said.
</P>
<P>
On the current situation in the country, the ICRC claimed,
"Insurgents have seized control of a quarter of the national
territory. In the south of the country, law and order are no
longer enforced and military bases have been abandoned to the
population. As a result, large numbers of people are armed."
</P>
<P>
The ICRC said that the Albanian Red Cross was delivering
medical aid and food to hospitals throughout the country,
including the areas of unrest. The ICRC has provided it with
essential surgical supplies for the treatment of 400
wounded. 
