<HEADLINE> Food Aid Starts Distributing in S. Somali Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 13 (xinhua)-- the distribution of a large
quantity of food aid started today in somalia's southwestern
region of Gedo, one of the most seriously drought hit places of
the country.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here said over 485 tons of miscellaneous
food aid including maize, beans and cooking oil were sent there
aiming at relieving more than 5,000 famine stricken families
living in the districts and villages of Gedo region that borders
on Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The emergency food aid was transported by 47 heavy duty trucks
which were warmly received by the people in the town of Badera
where the food first reached.
</P>
<P>
The escort of the food aid returned to Mogadishu after the
convoy reached Bardera and handed them to the local authorities
and representatives from the ICRC in the region.
</P>
<P>
The people of Bardera and Gedo region in general have sighed
with relief after the arrival of the food aid since the drought
was declared in many parts of the country two months ago.
