<HEADLINE> SADC Joint Exercise to Hold in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A joint Southern African
Development Community (SADC) peace-keeping training operation
dubbed Exercise Blue Hungwe gets underway at Nyanga on April 1,
Defense Minister Moven Mahachi said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe and South Africa will provide the bulk of the
soldiers for the exercise in eastern Zimbabwe, the first in
Africa, for which 727,000 U.S. Dollars has been pumped in to
enhance regional cooperation and military skills, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exercise comes at a time when the SADC inter-state defense
and security committee is in the process of developing standing
operating procedures for disaster management under the auspices
of the SADC organ on politics, defense and security chaired by
zimbabwean president robert mugabe.
</P>
<P>
Mahachi said, ''the post-cold war ushered in a new era where
peace support operations under the auspices of the U.N. are on
the increase.''
</P>
<P>
Invitations to the exercise being jointly sponsored by
Zimbabwe and the British government, have also been extended to
the region's police. 
</P>
