<HEADLINE> Britain Condemns Killing of Israeli Schoolgirls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The British government has
condemned the shooting of seven Israeli schoolgirls as "sickening"
but warned this incident should not trigger further violence.
</P>
<P>
The BBC television reported that a Jordanian soldier opened
fire as seven Israeli schoolgirls visited an observation post near
the Israeli-Jordanian border early today.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Malcolm Rifkind said in a statement
this afternoon, "I am deeply shocked and saddened by this tragic
loss of innocent Israeli children's lives. Such acts of violence
are sickening and universally deplored."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that this incident "should not spark further
violence and violence must not be allowed to jeopardize the
(Middle East) peace process."
</P>
<P>
"I am glad that the Jordanian and Israeli authorities are
working closely on the ground to bring the situation under
control," he added. 
</P>
