<HEADLINE> Greek Parliament Approves Bill on Schengen Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A bill on protecting privacy and
individual liberties, a condition for Greece's participation in
the Schengen Agreement, was passed in principle today by
parliament with 132 voting for and 89 against the bill.
</P>
<P>
