<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Form Specialised Police Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Republic Police
(ZRP) is forming a specialised tourism section to effectively
deal with criminal activities affecting the industry.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Hotel and Restaurant Association of Zimbabwe
Congress, ZRP Deputy Commissioner Enoch Ngwenya today said the
section, which will operate in all resort areas, will solely deal
with problems relating to tourists.
</P>
<P>
He said the ZRP has identified tourist muggings and
way-layings as areas which needed urgent attention.
</P>
<P>
''Criminal gangs may also use a ploy whereby they pose as
sculpture salesmen with one or two items. As soon as a tourist shows
interest the others mob the person ending in loss of purse and other
valuables,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He said gangs targeting tourists were also operating at airports,
major hotels and bureaux de change, while the motorised criminals
were becoming more violent and ruthless relying on mobility to avoid
detection.
</P>
<P>
Despite the manpower shortage, patrols have been increased to
achieve the objectives of the police service charter, a move which
has resulted in a marked reduction in tourist attacks, he said.
