<HEADLINE> Algerian Security Forces Kill 38 Islamic Militants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's security forces and
army killed 38 armed Islamic militants Wednesday in three
separate operations in and around the capital Algiers, said local
press reports.
</P>
<P>
Twelve extremists, including a women, who probably belonged to
the Armed Islamic Group, were killed in Beau-Fraisier, a district
located on the highland of Frais-Vallon in Algiers during a search
operation by security forces which lasted several hours.
</P>
<P>
Security forces also seized a large number of weapons from the
extremists, including automatic pistols and mini-machineguns, said
the reports.
</P>
<P>
Three armed individuals were killed Wednesday in the district
of Baba Ali of Algiers, while another group of 23 extremists were
killed by the Algerian army near Sour El-Ghozlane, in the suburb
of Algiers, said the press reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
