<HEADLINE> Lebanese President Receives Armenian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese President Elias Hrawi
received here this evening the visiting Foreign Minister of
Armenia Aleksandr Arzumanyan who conveyed a letter from the
Armenian head of state Ter Petrosyan on bilateral relations
and the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The letter says that Armenia will maintain a political and
moral support to Lebanon in seeking a settlement of the Middle
East problem, particularly the implementation of Security Council
resolution 425 on the unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Armenian President expressed his satisfaction with the
outcome of joint official cooperation among the ministries and
departments of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Armenian Minister of Foreign Affairs arrived in Beirut
earlier today on a one-day visit to Lebanon, coming from
Damascus. He had a meeting right after arrival with his Lebanese
counterpart Faris Bouez, dealing with bilateral relations,
Lebanon's stance on a Middle East settlement and the situation in
south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Following the 45-minute talks, the two sides signed a customs
agreement on the investments guarantees and non dual taxation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to newsmen after the talks, the Armenian Minister
expressed his pleasure with the Lebanese government decision to
open a Lebanese embassy in the Armenian capital city of
Yerevan. He said he was confident that the opening of the
Lebanese embassy would strengthen the ties of cooperation in all
fields between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic relations between Lebanon and Armenia are five years
old, and the two countries have concluded several agreements in
diverse fields. 
</P>
