<HEADLINE> Angolan War Refugees Abroad to Return Home from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 300,000 Angolan war
refugees abroad will begin to return home from May, said Albing
Malungo, the Minister of Assistance and Social Reinsertion, today.
</P>
<P>
Among all refugees, those staying in Zambia, The Congo and
Namibia will first return, he said after signing an aid accord
with the World Food Program.
</P>
<P>
The repatriation of refugees this year will estimatedly cost
the southern African country more than 30 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government, with the help of international
community, has set up bodies to provide basic social services to
refugees in some provinces and created all necessary conditions
for their return, said Malungo.
</P>
<P>
The refugees will come back home in safety and peace, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Currently there are 200,000 Angolan refugees in Zaire, 96,000
in Zambia, 12,000 in the Congo, 1,000 in Namibia and 15,000 in
other 32 countries. enditem


