reiterated his country's policy of good neighborliness and
endeavors to resolve differences with Uganda through peaceful
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
He added that the aggression committed by Ugandan troops
against the towns of Kaya and Yei along the Sudanese-Ugandan
borders last Sunday represented a flagrant violation of the
agreement reached between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese Minister added that despite the Sudan's keen
interest in the success of the Iranian mediation between the two
countries, the acts perpetrated by Uganda have rendered the talks
between the Sudan and Uganda, due to start in Kampala Saturday,
impossible.
</P>
<P>
He said Sudan has left the matter in the hands of Iran to have
the talks later in Nairobi or Kampala under better circumstances.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Iranian Foreign Minister Ali
Akbar Velayati arrived in Khartoum Wednesday on a one-day visit,
and handed a letter from Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani to
Sudanese President Omar Bashir, inviting him to participate in an
Islamic summit conference to be held in Tehran.
</P>
