<HEADLINE> HK to Enhance Anti-Drug Education Programs on Youths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Action Committee
Against Narcotics today endorsed 2.5 million HK dollars (322,580
US dollars) for 1997-98 anti-drug education programs among
youngsters.
</P>
<P>
The allocation of the fund for the program represents an
increase of 12 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Justein Wong Chun, chairman of the Education and Publicity
Sub-committee of the action committee, said that although there is
a drop in the number of young drug abusers in Hong Kong, his
sub-committee will continue to focus on the youth drug abuse
problem.
</P>
<P>
He said that the anti-drug program will comprise a wide variety
of educational, entertainment and sports activities with active
support committees, voluntary agencies, educational institutions,
the media and private organizations.
</P>
<P>
According to Wong, the programs will involve drug education
talks and a new video for the talks, anti-drug homepage on the
Internet, mobile publicity unit, workshops and seminars on
drug-prevention among youths, and district anti-drug campaigns.
</P>
</TEXT>
