<HEADLINE> European Countries Speed Up Evacuation Work in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- European countries and the United
States have asked their nationals to leave Albania as tension
heightened there.
</P>
<P>
France has sent four military transport helicopters to Albania
to evacuate 50 to 70 French nationals from the Balkan state to the
Italian city of Brindisi, said the office of chief of staff of the
French army. But the French government is not going to close its
embassy in Tirana.
</P>
<P>
A frigate of the French navy, Germinal, is sailing to the
Albanian coast to provide logistic support to the evacuation
operation, the same source added.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that a total of 700 foreign nationals have left
Albania by Italian military aircrafts and arrived in Italy over
the past 24 hours. Five Italian military aircrafts continued their
evacuation this morning.
</P>
<P>
European countries such as French and Italy have urged the
Albanian government and all political forces to work for a
solution to the crisis through dialogue and to take action to
prevent the loss of many weapons.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the Albania government and other political groups
have asked the international community to take action to control
the chaotic situation in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry officials of 15 EU countries held an emergency
meeting last night and issued a statement asking for effective
measures to curb violence and restore order.
</P>
<P>
This indicated that the EU had no plan for any military
intervention in the Balkan state.
</P>
<P>
NATO also issued a communique on Thursday calling for
prevention of further violence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
