<HEADLINE> HK Offers Best Value for Tourists' Shopping: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong offers excellent
value for visitors' shopping for luxury goods, according to the
latest Tourist Price survey conducted by the Economist
Intelligence Unit.
</P>
<P>
The survey says that Hong Kong emerges as the cheapest city
from 11 of the world's major tourist destinations, with prices
some 15 percent below the average cost for 15 selected tourist
items.
</P>
<P>
The latest survey, conducted at the end of 1996, is the 7th of
such pricing survey since 1992.
</P>
<P>
The survey obtains and analyzes the market prices a typical
tourist would have to pay in 11 cities for each of 15 selected
tourist items.
</P>
<P>
The cities include Hong Kong, Taibei, London, Bangkok, Tokyo,
Singapore, New York, Paris, Frankfurt, Toronto and Sydney, which
are ranked according to an index, calculated using the overall
mean average as the base.
</P>
<P>
The 15 selected items consist of celine handbag 1 (kelly),
celine handbag 2, Samsonite suitcase, Ralph Lauren polo shirt,
Chanel perfume, Bally men's dress shoes, Sony Discman, IBM
thinkpad, portable component system, Nintendo Gameboy, video
camera auto-focus camera, spectacle frames, gold necklace, Rolex
watch.
</P>
<P>
The survey says that Hong Kong remains the best place to buy
the type of tourist goods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
