<HEADLINE> STDs Cases Rise Among Ukrainian Teenagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The growth of sexually transmitted
diseases (STDs) has reached a new record among Ukrainian teenagers
over recent years with a nine-fold rise in AIDS-related patients
aged from 15 to 17.
</P>
<P>
Only 37 cases of HIV infection -- the virus that causes AIDS --
were registered among children aged from 15 to 17 in 1995. But by
August 1996, the number has shot up to 180, said Yuri Kruglov of
the country's Center for AIDS Prevention.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the World Health Organization (WHO) and Ukraine
called for improving the quality of the courses on value studies
and sexual knowledge in schools.
</P>
<P>
One expert, however, pointed out that the spread of STDs would
not ebb unless the country's social and economic circumstances
improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
