<HEADLINE> Northeast China's First Test-tube Baby Born In Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's first
test-tube baby was born last night in the capital of Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
Weighing 3,200 grams and measuring 56 centimeters, the baby boy
is doing well following his birth at the Shenyang Peace District
Woman and Baby Hospital, which has established a first-class
reproduction medical research center to study advanced
reproduction technology in the world.
</P>
<P>
The baby's mother was unable to conceive naturally, due to a
medical condition.
</P>
<P>
China's first test-tube baby was born in Beijing in 1988; there
are now more than 250 test-tube babies in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
