<HEADLINE> s f s 1957 China-Li Peng-Meeting-3 Li Peng Meets Press (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Concerning the question how China will handling the incident of
Hwang Jang-yop, Li said the incident occurred in China, and that
in accordance with the universally-recognized conventions of the
international law, China, as a sovereign state, has the full right
of jurisdiction over the incident.
</P>
<P>
"For the same reason, China does not recognize the right of
diplomatic asylum by foreign embassies and consulates in its
territory," Li Peng said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side is very prudent in handling this incident,
mainly proceeding from the question of maintaining peace and
stability on the Korean Peninsular, according to the premier.
</P>
<P>
In the entire course of handling this case, Li said, "We
should, of course, take into account the stances of all the
parties concerned, and resolve the issue properly as soon as
possible in accordance with the relevant international laws.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the conditions are almost ripe for resolving
this incident," Li said.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the question on how China will solve the
remaining problems of state-owned enterprises, Li put forward a
total of seven measures for the reform of state firms in his
Government Work Report. "Those measures are all to the point and
feasible, and are in line with the experiences of state enterprise
reform in the past years," he said.
</P>
<P>
An important measure taken by the government this year is to
support major large and medium-sized state-owned firms and enliven
small ones by giving them greater freedom and flexibility of
operation, by which the government expects to achieve positive
results, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The task in the future is to step up the reform and improve
management of some loss-making firms, he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier also noted that problems some state firms now face
have existed for a long time and will not be solved overnight. "It
will take a long time to address the problems," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
