<HEADLINE> Albanian Soldiers, Police Ordered to Report to Units </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The new Albanian government today
ordered all soldiers and policemen to return to their units and be
ready to defend the country.
</P>
<P>
The national reconciliation government, set up on Wednesday,
issued an appeal on TV to the whole nation, ordering all active
and retired servicemen and policemen to immediately report to
their units and undertake the "holy mission of defending the
motherland."
</P>
<P>
The appeal said that the country "is in danger."
</P>
<P>
Armed violence broken out across the Balkan state and the
situation is deteriorating rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Almost all soldiers and policemen have returned home after
nationwide protests turned into street violence, which quickly
spread from the south to other areas of the country. 
