<HEADLINE> South Africa Beats Switzerland in World Cup Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 14 (Xinhua) -- South Africa edged
Switzerland 3-2 to finish tenth at the World Cup Field Hockey
Qualifying Round here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two goals from Mike Cullan in the fifth and the 32nd
minutes put the Africans 2-0 ahead at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland reduced the deficit as Beni Steinemann scored in
the 41st minute.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's Brenton Key had a goal in the 52nd minute, while
one minute later Christian Cavallet scored for Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
In the other match, Argentina beat Belgium 2-1 to get the
seventh place, Canada defeated Malaysia 3-1 for the fifth place,
while Belarus defeated Ireland 2-1 to score 11th position in the
12-nation meet. The top four positions will be decided on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Spain, South Korea, New Zealand, Poland, Canada and Malaysia
have already won the six berths for the World Cup finals in
Utrecht, the Netherlands from May 20 to 31 next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
