<HEADLINE> U.S. Temporarily Suspends Evacuation Mission in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States has
temporarily suspended its evacuation mission in the chaotic
Albania after its helicopters were fired on, CNN reported.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. helicopters, sent in to pick out the American citizens
stranded in Albania, are vulnerable targets of ground missiles  1
in day time operations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A U.S. Cobra gunship returned fire today.
</P>
<P>
An Italian AB-212 helicopter, on an evacuation mission, was
reportedly hit by small gun fire from the ground today, but no one
aboard was injured.
</P>
<P>
About 408 American citizens have been flown out of Albania
where the situation is deteriorating rapidly. There are still some
2,000 Americans waiting to be evacuated.
</P>
<P>
CNN said nearly everybody on Tirana streets is heavily armed as
they expected neither the army nor the police to provide security
for them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
