<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing People Happy, Sober-Minded about NPC Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Government officials and people
of the just-approved Chongqing municipality appear happy but
sober-minded at the news of the establishment of Chongqing as a
centrally-administered municipality in accordance with a decision
made by the Eighth National People's Congress at its
just-concluded fifth session.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing city and three largely rural areas that have just
been incorporated into the municipality used to be part of Sichuan
province.
</P>
<P>
When news of the NPC decision reached Chongqing today, local
officials and people expressed agreement that Chongqing should
play the role of serving as an economic center in southwest china,
of doing a good job in relocating the one million people around
the Three Gorges Project area, and of developing economy in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhizhong, deputy secretary of the municipal Party
committee, said establishment of the municipality is a major step
taken by the central authorities to accelerate economic
development in central and western China.
</P>
<P>
He said Chongqing shoulders heavy responsibilities and will
strive for quicker development.
</P>
<P>
Said Xu Zhongming, vice mayor of Chongqing in charge of
opening-up, said: "We are fully aware of the pressure after
Chongqing becomes a centrally-administered municipality."
</P>
<P>
He said that Chongqing will open wider to the outside world,
effectively improve its environmental investment, and attract more
domestic and overseas businesses to start operations in Chongqing
and the area around the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing has established a Relocation Bureau to handle the
resettlement of people affected by the Project.
</P>
<P>
Liu Fuyin, director of the bureau, said establishment of
Chongqing municipality will facilitate centralized planning and
management of the resettlement program.
</P>
<P>
Ren Dajun, secretary of the newly-established Rural Work
Committee of Chongqing Municipal Party Committee, said that, since
the new municipality has a vast rural area, the municipality's
urban areas will do a good job of galvanizing economic development
in the rural area.
</P>
<P>
People in the two cities of Wanxian and Fuling and the
prefecture of Qianjiang, which have been incorporated into
Chongqing municipality, also voiced their approval for the NPC
decision.
</P>
<P>
Shui Zhengkuan, secretary of the Qianjiang Prefectural Party
Committee, said Qianjiang is a poor area with 1.06 million people
living under the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that the local authorities are determined to lift
these people out of poverty within the three years before the
start of the next century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
