<HEADLINE> HK to Hold International Golden Mile Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The 12th Hong Kong
international Golden Mile race organized by the Hong Kong Amateur
Athletic Association will be held on Sunday at Chater Road
Pedestrian Precinct, central Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Runners from 11 countries and cities are to compete for the
Bank of China Group Cup men's international invitational race.
</P>
<P>
As for the international women's race, Zeng Yuying from south
China's Guangdong province will again take part in the event.
</P>
<P>
The runner-up in 1994 turned out third in 1995 and she came
back strong last year for the second place, with a personal best
performance of four minutes 42 seconds.
</P>
<P>
With a personal best of 4:11 in 1,500 meters, Zhang Jinqing,
20, from north China's Hebei province, and Britain's 24-year-old
defending champion Shirley Griffiths, who has a personal best of
4:11 for 1,500 meters, are expected to demonstrate a real
show-down.
</P>
<P>
The Golden Mile includes 11 categories: men's and women's
international races, local men's and women's open races, veteran
races, interport schoolboys' and schoolgirls' races, inter-bank
relay and inter-school's boys' and girls' races.  
</P>
