<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cheers to Birth of China's Fourth Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The decision to upgrade
Chongqing, a major industrial city in southwest China, to be the
country's fourth municipality, a motion which merits worldwide
attention, was approved at the Fifth Session of the National
People's Congress (NPC), China's legislature, today.
</P>
<P>
When Qiao Shi, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee announced
the approval of the motion at 3:54 hours this afternoon, the grand
auditorium in the Great Hall of the People resounded with
thunderous applauses.
</P>
<P>
Photographers and cameramen from both China and overseas
snapped the historical moment and transmitted it to the audience
and viewers around the world.
</P>
<P>
"The motion has been approved! The motion has been approved!"
claimed Jiang Weining, a TV reporter from Chongqing Television
Station excitedly through his mobile phone to his fellow residents
in Chongqing. And an enthusiastic response with prolonged cheers
was heard on the phone instantly.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Chongqing, China's largest city in the upper Yangtze
River Valley and a leading industrial city in southwest China is
endowed with a mission as a "bellwether" of enlivening the economy
in the central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
"Though we 'break up' our family, we'll still have deep
affections for each other and will be good neighbors for ever,"
said Yu Hanqing, director of the Standing Committee of Chongqing
Municipal People's Congress, while having cordial hand-shakes with
Xie Shijie, party secretary of the Sichuan Provincial Party
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan covered an area of 570,000 sq km with a population of
110 million yesterday. And it gives away 82,000 sq km with 30
million people to Chongqing with the approval to establish the
latter as the fourth centrally-administered municipality today.
</P>
<P>
He Zhiqiang, governor of southwestern Yunnan province sat
nearby when the motion was approved. He congratulated Yu and said
with joy, "We'd march hand in hand in the future."
</P>
<P>
The promoted Chongqing has now been entrusted with three major
responsibilities, namely, to give scope to the role of the center
on the Yangtze's upper reaches, explore a new road for cities to
help adjacent rural areas, and to fulfil the relocation of farmers
from the Three George Project area.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zongli, president of the Shanghai Academy of Social
Sciences, pitched in and said with excitement,"Such upgrading is
necessitated by the economic take-off in the Yangtze River
valley."
</P>
<P>
When NPC deputies walked out of the Great Hall of the People,
the venue of NPC's annual session, after the session is over,
Zhang Deling, party secretary of the newly-established Chongqing
Municipality, was soon surrounded by crowds of long-waiting
reporters, who bombarded him with a chain of questions. Smiling
Zhang said repeatedly,"My responsibility overweighs my joy."
</P>
<P>
Huang Ji, a NPC deputy and famous writer from Chongqing, who
has just completed his new reportoire "the Birth of Chongqing
Municipality from Diaries of a NPC Deputy" ended his works with a
real happy ending: "Wish you Good luck, my Chongqing!"  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
