<HEADLINE> East China Trade Fair Ends With 2.2 Billion Dollars Deals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The annual regional export trade
fair in east China ended today here in Shanghai, with deals worth
2.23 billion US dollars clinched.
</P>
<P>
Attended by nearly 8,000 business people from 125 countries and
regions, the fair was the biggest of its kind in the booming east
China region.
</P>
<P>
Most transactions fell into the categories of oil and cereals,
local and animal by-produce, textiles, hardware and chemicals. New
and hi-tech products were among the more favorable items sold here.
</P>
<P>
Japan and the European Union became the biggest buyers for the
eastern provinces, and the trade volume with Singapore, Malaysia,
and Middle East increased by 11 percent, 39 percent and 31.2
percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The trade with Taiwan region, Latin America and Africa also
witnessed a sharp rise at the fair.  
</P>
