<HEADLINE> Clinton to Undergo Tendon Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
tore a tendon in his knee early today after stumbling on steps at
the home of golf pro Greg Norman in Florida and will undergo
surgery to repair the damage.
</P>
<P>
The damage to his right knee was described as substantial and
Clinton's doctor said he had to undergo a surgery late this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Clinton stumbled on a step as he left Norman's home and tore
his quadriceps tendon.
</P>
<P>
His doctors said he will be in a leg brace and crutches for
two to six weeks.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is expected to meet with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin in Helsinki on March 19-20. It was unclear whether he
would be able to attend the summit now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
