<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are business briefs
from Middle East countries:
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey's office of the General Staff and the
Undersecretariat for the Defense Industry are working on a
proposal to transfer the U.S. shares in F-16 producer Turkish
Aerospace Industries (TAI)to Koc Holding, the largest industrial
company in the country.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Turkey have reached an agreement, under which the
40 percent of U.S. shares in TAI would be transferred to Turkey
when the F-16 fighter production program ends.
</P>
<P>
RABAT -- an international conference on water, the first of its
kind, is due to be held in Morocco from March 20-26 to tackle the
shortage of sweet water on the international level.
</P>
<P>
The conference to be held under the motto of "Water For Us and
For the Coming Generations" will also assess the global water needs
in the coming century.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt and Italy will establish later this month an
investments promotion union at a cost of 2 million LE (some
600,000 US dollars) to assist cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government had appropriated 70 million LE (about 20
million US dollars) in credit facilities to cover the costs of the
union's activities, according to the local press today.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt and the European Union reached an agreement
Thursday, which allows 103 Egyptian commodities including 85
traditional commodities and 10 agricultural products to enter the
European markets.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here in Cairo after lengthy
partnership negotiations between the two sides, the local
newspaper Al Ahram reported today.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- France's Minister of Industry, Energy and
Communication Frank Prutora is scheduled to arrive in the Egyptian
capital for a two-day visit to seek closer cooperation in electric
power generation.
</P>
<P>
A protocol is expected to be signed at the end of Frank's
visit, the local press reported today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
