<HEADLINE> New Airbus Joins Eastern Airlines Fleet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An A340-300 jet of the Airbus
family arrived at the Shanghai Airport on March 13, the fourth
such long-range airplane bought by the Shanghai-based Eastern
Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Eastern plans to purchase eight A340-300s, the passenger
airplane with the longest flying range in the world, during the
1996-2000 period. The first jet of the airlines was delivered
by Airbus Industrie in May of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Topping all its rivals in terms of the flying range, the
A340-300 can make non-stop flights between any Chinese airport and
North America. Moreover, the airplane is equipped with an advanced
flight operating system which is controlled by high-speed
computers.
</P>
<P>
The sixth A340-300 will join the fleet of Eastern Airlines in
June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
