<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host World Tourism Leaders' Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine Tourism Department
and the World Tourism Organization have agreed to organize a World
Tourism Leaders' Meeting in Manila on May 22, the Philippine News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Around 500 to 700 Tourism Ministers, eminent international
professionals and chief executive officers in the private sector
are expected to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A number of international and regional organizations will also
be involved, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Tourism Secretary Mina Gabor was quoted as saying
that the meeting is a very timely initiative on the part of the
Philippine Government considering that top tourism leaders
worldwide will discuss the cultural and social impact of tourism.
</P>
<P>
Philippine President Fidel Ramos has been invited as the
keynote speaker during the opening ceremony, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will adopt the Manila Declaration on the Social
Impacts of Tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
