<HEADLINE> Japan Wins Queen Sirikit Cup Women's Golf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Japan won the team trophy of the
Queen Sirikit Cup Asian women's golf invitational tournament for
the fifth time here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Japan scored a total of 442, followed by runner-up South Korea
at 446. New Zealand was third at 454.
</P>
<P>
Kimiyo Yoshida had 72 and Mayumi Nakajima had 76 on the
concluding day to boost Japan to the victory.
</P>
<P>
Australian Kate Macintosh took the individual title with 218,
two strokes ahead of Philippines' Jennifer Rosales. Japan's Mie
Nakata, who had one-under-par 70 Thursday, had a poor 78 Friday to
come third at 221.
</P>
<P>
China placed ninth among the 11 competing teams here, while its
golfers Hu Xiangzhen and Zhang Lichun was equally ranked 16th.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event, named after Thailand's Queen Sirikit, was
inaugurated in Bangkok, Thailand, in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Next year's event will be held in Bombay, India. 
</P>
</TEXT>
