<HEADLINE> Seven Killed, 15 Injured in India Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- At least seven people were
killed and 15 others injured when a powerful bomb exploded today
at a railway station outside Jalandhar city, about 250 km
northwest of New Delhi, capital of India, the Press Trust of India
(PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The deaths included one policeman and three cycle
rickshaw-pullers, the report said. The cause of the blast is not
immediately known. 
