<HEADLINE> Best English Speaker Chosen in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-two Chinese college
students participated in today's second "21st Century Cup"
National English-Speaking Competition here, demonstrating their
oratorial skills on the topic "Me, My Country and the World."
</P>
<P>
First place winner was 20-year-old Li Shu from Sichuan Union
University.
</P>
<P>
Li, together with the second prize winner Zhu Hong, from Fudan
University, received a scholarship to travel to Britain to attend
the annual international English-speech competition, which will be
held by the English-Speaking Union in London this May.
</P>
<P>
At today's competition, the contestants each presented a
prepared speech on the given topic, followed by a three-minute
impromptu speech and a three-minute question and answer session
with the judges.
</P>
<P>
The most important contest of its kind in China is meant to
boost English education in the country, and promote cultural
exchanges between China and other countries, especially
English-speaking nations, said the sponsor, China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Last year's first place winner was Liu Xin from Nanjing
University, who also took the golden cup at the London
international speech competition in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
