<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Network Equipment Supplier Heading For Larger Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Network Equipment Technology
Inc. (NET), one of the leading US suppliers of data telecom
network facilities, has found a profitable market in China, a
country in the midst of sweeping telecom reforms.
</P>
<P>
So far, the company has developed into the biggest provider for
Chinanet, one of three national-level public telecom networks here.
</P>
<P>
The NET data transmission products are used in the public and
private networks in Sichuan, Inner Mongolia, Zhejiang and Fujian,
however, the company is looking forward to a bigger market share
here.
</P>
<P>
NET introduced its ATM (asynchronous transport mode) products
to China in order to facilitate the online services and
multi-media transmission, according to representatives with the NET
China office.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, they said, the company will provide stronger
technical support for its Chinese sales agents, and expand the
cooperation with local partners in the fields of engineering and
personnel training.
</P>
<P>
NET will establish its second representative office in China in
Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province, later this year.
</P>
<P>
The company's global turnover came to 3.4 billion US dollars in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
