<HEADLINE> France to Evacuate French Nationals in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 14 (Xinhua) -- France will send four military
transport helicopters to Albania today to evacuate 50 to 70 French
nationals from the Balkan state to the Italian city of Brindisi,
said the office of chief of staff of the French army.
</P>
<P>
A frigate of the French navy, Germinal, is sailing to the
Albanian coast to provide logistic support to the evacuation
operation, said the same source.
</P>
<P>
The Agence France-Presse said that 69 foreigners, most of them
French, were evacuated this morning from Tirana and are now in
Durres, 40 kilometers south of Tirana, where they will be lifted
by the French helicopters. 
