<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola's New TB Contractors Top 10,867 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- New tuberculosis contractors in
Angola last year reached 10,867, according to the statistics
published by the Ministry of Health here today.
</P>
<P>
Although the figure was quite high compared to 6,623
contractors in 1995, people here consider it too low as Jorge
Dupret, director of the National TB Prevention Authority,
estimated that new TB contractors last year should be 20,000.
</P>
<P>
He said 3,400 TB contractors appeared alone in Luanda
province, one of the 18 provinces in the country.
</P>
<P>
Dupret attributed the fast increase of the disease to the
chaos brought about by large numbers of refugees during the civil
war, and malnutrition resulting in the decline of people's
immunity from illness.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Instability enables people to move from rural to
urban areas, and there is lack of both doctors and medicines in
hospitals of the country. Only four specialists throughout Angola
look after 400 in-patients and there are 100 out-patients every
day.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organization said out of 3.354 million
tuberculosis patients at present in the world, 541,360 are
Africans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
