<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lhasa Starts to Optimize Assets of State Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Lhasa, capital city of Tibet
Autonomous Region, today launched an experimental program to
optimize the structure of local state-owned firms' assets.
</P>
<P>
This was announced at a local meeting in Lhasa today. Xu
Mingyang, vice-chairman of the regional government told the
meeting that the program represents a turning point for Tibet's
enterprise restructuring, as it will change from the practice of
restructuring a single company to invigorating the entire
state-owned sector of the city.
</P>
<P>
As the regional political, economic and cultural center, the
Tibetan capital represents 60 percent of the autonomous region's
total number of state firms and 70 percent of their assets,
according to the vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the enterprise reform in Tibet relies on the
pilot reform in Lhasa, which will be of great importance for
attaining the goal of the autonomous region's Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000) and its long-term objective for the year 2010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
