<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mini Primary Schools to Be Set Up in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education and the
UNICEF have decided to set up mini-primary schools in Angola to
take care of urban street children and rural kids.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken at a workshop here last night jointly
sponsored by the ministry and the U.N. Children's Fund in the
Angolan capital.
</P>
<P>
Mini-primary schools should be set up in refugees concentrated
areas with tents or makeshift huts and they should not be more
than one kilometer away from where the children live, the
workshop said.
</P>
<P>
It urged central and provincial organs to take part in the
realization of the strategic target of national education:
increase of school opportunities for children and improvement of
education quality.
</P>
<P>
The workshop also demanded each and every of the 18 provinces
in Angola works out education promotion plan for 1997-1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
