<HEADLINE> China's Pharmaceutical Industry's Output Up For 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- China's pharmaceutical industry
turned out 120 billion yuan in output value in 1996, up 15 percent
from 1995, according to an official with the State Pharmaceutical
Administration.
</P>
<P>
The official told a three-day international medical conference
that China's sales of medical goods amounted to 80 billion yuan
last year, up 12 percent from 1995, a sign that the medical care
system has improved.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which opened in Beijing Wednesday, has
attracted 80 business executives and senior managers of
pharmaceutical producers in the world and 120 Chinese
pharmaceutical specialists, according to Health Daily.
</P>
<P>
It wad jointly sponsored by the international exchange centers
of the Public Health Ministry and the State Pharmaceutical Bureau
and HPC International Medical Information Company (Hong Kong).
</P>
<P>
Overseas experts will speak on general trends in the world
pharmaceutical market, marketing strategies, and quality, and
Chinese representatives will discuss developments in the Chinese
pharmaceutical industry.
</P>
<P>
Chen Minzhang, the Chinese minister of Public Health, and Zheng
Xiaoyu, director of the State Pharmaceutical Administration also
spoke at the conference. 
</P>
