<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by another 18.87 points to close at 2135.46
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 181.07 million units, worth
461.65 million Singapore dollars (about 320.59 million US
dollars). Declines again overwhelmed advances by 271 to 71, while
266 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Sin Soon Huat was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 14.69 million units. It was followed by Noble which
had 9.58 million shares traded. Ber Ind. was next with 7.83
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sembawang led the gainers of the day as it rose by 70
cents to finish at 31.1 Singapore dollars. NBT increased by 40
cents to end at 8.35 Singapore dollars, while UMW warrant closed
30 cents higher at 4.3 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the biggest loser as it declined by one Singapore dollar to 26.6
Singapore dollars. Samanda Holdings fell by 70 cents to end at 6.9
Singapore dollars, while the Keppel Corporation hs warrant97
finished 52 cents lower at 1.08 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
