the most popular annual event in Hong Kong for horticulturists and
flower lovers, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's show is "A Hong Kong Spectacular of
Cosmopolitan Blossoms," said Lam Wai-keung, chairman of the
Regional Council, co-organizer of the event.
</P>
<P>
"The exhibits include a wide range of exotic flora, many
beautiful displays of flowering plants from different parts of the
world and a collection of different species of this year's theme
flower, Lady's Slipper Orchid," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The show also provides many interesting activities such as
talks and demonstrations on horticulture, drawing competitions,
photographic competitions, a variety of games for children and
other related activities," he added.
</P>
<P>
The 10-day floral extravaganza at Sha Tin Park and Sha Tin Town
 Hall is being organized jointly by the Regional and Urban
Councils.
</P>
<P>
The colorful displays are presented by more than 70 local and
overseas horticultural organizations, including those from the
Chinese mainland, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Flower Show has been growing in scale and
popularity since its debut in 1987. Last year, the show attracted
over 480,000 visitors. 
