<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Blood Donors in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The number of blood donors in Macao
 has been on the rise over the past nine years, to reach nearly
8,000 in 1996, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, only 1,250 people donated blood. But that figure rose
continuously to 5,518 in 1992 and 7,797 in 1996, a top executive
of the Macao Blood Donation Center told the "Tai Chung Pou"
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Among the blood donors in 1996, 36 percent were women, and 47
percent were under the age of 26.
</P>
<P>
The donated blood can meet the needs of local hospitals, which
require an average of 600 bags of blood a month, according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
The blood donors include students, hotel workers, government
employees and bank clerks.
</P>
<P>
No HIV-positive donors were found although some people were
tested hepatitis B.
</P>
<P>
The government plans to build a new blood donation center in
1998 to house more testing facilities, says the report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
