<HEADLINE> 43 Million People Infected with Hepatitis-B in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An estimated 43 million people
in India are infected with hepatitis-B virus (HBV), said a survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey report was made available to the press here today by
Smithkline Beecham, the sole manufacturer of "engerix B," the only
hepatitis-B virus vaccine.
</P>
<P>
HBV infection was a hundred times more infectious than AIDS.
While AIDS awareness was increasing, HBV, the silent killer, was
stalking society, a panel of doctors said.
</P>
<P>
The HBV accounted for an estimated 340,000 deaths in India
every year, the panel said.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organization (WHO) has expressed concern over
the severity of attacks and low level of awareness.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
