<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China is Stable Politically: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(Eds: This is the full text of Li's opening remarks in
meeting with reporters)
</P>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The new generation of China's
collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core has the support
of the people of the whole country, Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark during a meeting with Chinese and overseas
journalists shortly after the closing of the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress. The full text of Li's opening
remarks at the meeting are as follows:
</P>
<P>
The current session of the National People's Congress, which
had come to a successful conclusion, just approved the report on
the work of the government last year I delivered on behalf of the
State Council. The fifth session of the Eighth National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
also voiced its endorsement to the government work report and its
support to the future work.
</P>
<P>
"The future tasks for the State Council and governments at all
levels are to implement the objectives, goals and measures set
forth in this report and, with the support of the people across
the country, to do still better the work for this year.
</P>
<P>
Our beloved Comrade Deng Xiaoping passed away shortly before
the convocation of the sessions of the NPC and the National
Committee of the CPPCC, and the entire mourning activities,
proceeding in an air of solemnity, were immersed in deepest grief
and held in an orderly way, giving an expression to the people's
profound respects for Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Judging from the proceedings of the two sessions of NPC and
CPPCC respectively, we can see that the current collective
leadership with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core has the support of
the entire Chinese people and China's political situation is
stable.
</P>
<P>
We are convinced that the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics initiated by Comrade Deng Xiaoping is
sure to be carried forward and continue to be developed, and
China's situation will become better and better.  
</P>
</TEXT>
