<HEADLINE> S. African Police Cracks Massive Driving License </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The South African police
has cracked a massive fraud scheme in which people who cannot
even interpret road signs have obtained driving licenses, local
daily the Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of licences have been sold to truck and bus drivers,
taxi operators and ordinary drivers, for amounts ranging between
800 Rands (181 U.S. Dollars) and 1600 Rands (362 U.S. Dollars) by
a syndicate involving government officials and staff of driving
schools, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Several people involving the fraud have been arrested in the
past few weeks while more arrests are expected, the paper quoted
police sources as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
