<HEADLINE> Li Expresses Confidence in Reform of State Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here today that the Chinese Government has confidence in the
ongoing reform of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Li put forward a total of seven measures for the reform of
state firms in his Government Work Report. "Those measures are all
to the point and feasible, and are in line with the experiences of
state enterprise reform in the past years," he told reporters
after the conclusion of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
An important measure taken by the government this year is to
support major large and medium-sized state firms and enliven small
ones by giving them greater freedom and flexibility of operation,
by which the government expects to achieve positive results, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
The task in the future is to step up the reform and improve
management of some loss-making firms, he said.
</P>
<P>
The premier also noted that problems some state firms now
face have existed for a long time and will not be solved overnight.
"It will take a long time to address the problems," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
