<HEADLINE> Indian Trade Show Opens in Nepali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An Indian Trade Exhibition
opened here today with the objective to enhance bilateral trade
between the two neighbors and explore possibilities of increasing
Nepal's export to India.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day exhibition, organized by the Indian Trade
Promotion Organization, will bring together about 100 Indian
companies to display items including agriculture machinery,
aviation technology, automobiles, computers, chemicals, electrical
and electronic goods and garments.
</P>
