<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Provinces, Ministries Not to Interfere in HKSAR Affairs: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that the relevant Chinese provinces and ministries should
not interfere in the affairs of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) after Hong Kong's return to the
embrace of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Li told a group of domestic and overseas reporters, who are
here reporting on the current session of the Chinese legislative
body, that after July 1 this year, HKSAR will be a special
administrative region with a high degree of autonomy, toward which
China will adopt the policy of "One country, two systems" and
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
Thus, he added, "no provinces and ministries will be allowed to
interfere in HKSAR's affairs."
</P>
<P>
Li noted that some people from the British side claimed recently
that they would supervise over the implementation of the
Sino-British Joint Declaration on Hong Kong issue after July 1.
</P>
<P>
"This is not realistic, as the issue of Hong Kong will be
purely China's internal affair after the country resumes the
exercise of its sovereignty over the region on July 1 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
