<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annual NPC Session Closes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The annual session of the
National People's Congress (NPC), the Chinese legislature, closed
here today after two weeks of deliberations on reports submitted
by the government and adoption of a series of resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Deputies to the Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC deliberated the
government work report delivered by Premier Li Peng, a report on
the implementation of the 1996 national economic and social
development plan and a 1997 plan for national economic and social
development, a report on the implementation of the central and
local budgets for 1996 and central and local budgets for 1997, and
made some revisions to the reports.
</P>
<P>
The deputies approved of the central and local budgets for
1997, and passed resolutions approving revised reports.
</P>
<P>
Also adopted by the session is an amended Criminal Law and a
Defense Law. The amended Criminal Law will come into effect on
October 1, 1997, while the Defense Law takes effect on the day of
its promulgation.
</P>
<P>
The session also passed a decision on the quota allocation and
election of deputies to the Ninth NPC, and a method for the
election of deputies from the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) to the Ninth NPC. Besides, the session made a
decision approving the establishment of Chongqing as a
centrally-administered municipality.
</P>
<P>
The session also adopted five resolutions, approving
respectively: a work report of the NPC Standing Committee, a work
report of the Supreme People's Court, a work report of the Supreme
People's Procuratorate, a report on the NPC Standing Committee's
inspection of enforcement of the Agriculture Law, and a work
report of the NPC Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The deputies maintained that a summary of past year's work made
in the government work report tallies with realities, and tasks as
outlined in the report for the new year are feasible. Based on
deputies' suggestions, about 15 revisions and additions have been
made to the report.
</P>
<P>
While adopting the national economic and social development
plan and central and local budgets for 1997, the session requires
governments at all levels to firmly and conscientiously implement
guiding principles and policies formulated by the central
authorities, and focus economic work on promoting the two
fundamental changes, improving the quality and efficiency of
economic growth and seeking steady progress, to bring about a
sustained, rapid and healthy development of national economy.
</P>
<P>
The session also requires governments at all levels to strictly
implement the budgets, and strengthen the restraining force of the
budgets.
</P>
</TEXT>
