<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annual NPC Session Closes (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, described the
session as successful, democratic, practical, united and
encouraging.
</P>
<P>
The session is of particularly important significance for
mobilizing people of all ethnic groups to unswervingly march
forward on the road of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics initiated by Deng Xiaoping and to score new
victories in the drive of reform, opening up and modernization,
Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
Deputies to this year's session showed great concern about
reform of state-owned enterprises, economic restructuring and a
steady development of agriculture, and put forward a lot of
valuable opinions and proposals, he said.
</P>
<P>
These problems are a reflection of deep-layer contradictions in
reform and development, are problems on the path of progress and
are imperative problems that call for immediate solutions, Qiao
said.
</P>
<P>
The key to fundmentally solving these problems lies in
deepening reforms and accomplishing a successful shift in the
economic structure and economic growth mode, he noted.
</P>
<P>
With objectives set forth during the session in mind, a good
job should be done in all aspects of work, in order to
continuously promote a sustained, rapid and healthy development of
the national economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also called for efforts to promote ethical and cultural
progress and to promote the progress of all social undertakings.
</P>
<P>
He urged deputies to sincerely study and grasp Deng Xiaoping's
thinking on developing democracy and a legal system and to push
such development to a new stage in the spirit of reform.
</P>
<P>
The key to strengthening the building of socialist democracy
and a socialist legal system lies in doing everything in strict
accordance with the Constitution and other laws, or in other
words, governing the country by law, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
People's congresses at all levels should continue to speed up
the pace of legislation and improve the quality of legislation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to continuously strengthen
supervision, in order to ensure law enforcement, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao called on deputies to work hard to greet the return of
Hong Kong to the motherland and the convening of the 15th National
Congress of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
"We will carry work forward at the behest of Comrade Deng
Xiaoping and rally more closely round the CPC Central Committee
with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core under the guidance of the
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and the
basic line of the Party," Qiao said, calling for further efforts
to deepen reforms, open wider to the outside world and push ahead
with socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided over by Qiao Shi.
</P>
<P>
Party and government leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Li Ruihuan,
Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren were present at
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,720 deputies attended the closing meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
