<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Mediators to Work on Albania's Unrest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An emergency talk between Albanian
officials and European mediators would begin today on an Italian
warship off Albania's coast, it was reported here.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Franz Vranitzky, who had arrived at the
Italian port of Brindisi, would fly to the warship by helicopter.
</P>
<P>
New Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim Fino and other senior
Albanian officials had already got on board the warship, it added.
</P>
<P>
Leading a 10-member delegation of the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe, Vranitzky, former Austrian chancellor,
is also going to talk with other political leaders and rebel
representatives.
</P>
<P>
Albania has been in the grip of unrest since January after the
collapse of pyramid investment schemes in which thousands of
Albanians lost their life savings.
</P>
<P>
The protest turned violent two weeks ago as rebels looted
weapons from army depots. Several cities in southern Albania are
now controlled by rebels who are threatening to move onto the
capital.
</P>
<P>
Tirana itself has also witnessed growing unrest as mobs looted
a warehouse of 650 tons of flour on Thursday and raided security
force depots in search of guns.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Sali Berisha on Thursday decided to deploy
tanks in front of the main institutions in the country and called
for foreign military intervention to halt the disorder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
