<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Stresses Importance of Socialist Democracy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
legislative body, hailed the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress (NPC), which closed here today, as a great
success.
</P>
<P>
In his remarks at the closing meeting today, Qiao said the
current session is of great significance for mobilizing people of
all ethnic groups to unswervingly march forward along the road of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated by Deng
Xiaoping to strive for new victories in reform, opening up and the
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
said deputies have showed great concern over, and put forward lots
of good suggestions for, reform of state-owned enterprises and for
a sustained development of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The key to solving these problems, he said, is to deepen reform
and achieve fundamental shifts in economic structure and economic
growth mode. Reform of the state sector is the focus of this
year's economic restructuring, he said.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee chairman urged the nation to
steadfastly strengthen agriculture as the foundation of the
national economy, protect farmers' enthusiasm for production and
adopt more effective measures to ease their financial burden.
</P>
<P>
He told the deputies to work hard to promote a sustained, rapid
and healthy national economic development in line with goals set
at the current NPC session and promote cultural, ethical and
social progresses in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
"The historical moment for China to resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong is close at hand," said Qiao, calling
for great efforts to ensure a smooth transfer of power in Hong
Kong and its smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
He said China will strictly abide by the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and live up to policies
of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of
autonomy for the HKSAR under the principle of "one country, two
systems."
</P>
<P>
He expressed his confidence that Hong Kong will maintain
long-term prosperity and stability with an increasingly prosperous
motherland providing powerful backing and the joint efforts of the
six million intelligent and diligent Hong Kong compatriots.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Stresses Importance of Socialist Democracy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao pointed out that Deng Xiaoping's thinking on developing a
democratic legal system is a very important part of his theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping had considered it a long-term goal and basic
principle of the Party to persist in developing democracy and a
legal system, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
"Without democracy, there would neither be socialism nor
socialist modernization. Like modernization, democratization must
be developed step by step. The more developed socialism is, the
greater democracy, " Qiao quoted Deng Xiaoping as saying.
</P>
<P>
Deng also stressed the importance of strengthening the legal
system to protect people's democracy and called for a
systemization of democracy and the enshrining of democratic
principles in law, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Deng also held that issues relating to systems are
more important and more essential. Deng had urged to enact a
series of laws, decrees and regulations to fundamentally ensure
the democratization of the political life of the Party and the
state, of economic administration and of entire social life, so as
to guarantee an orderly progression of the entire society.
</P>
<P>
"These theories of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's are profound and
very important, and we must study them conscientiously, gain a
better understanding of them and implement them unequivocally in
order to turn them into action to promote the development of
socialist democracy and a socialist legal system to a new stage
under the spirit of reform," said Qiao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Stresses Importance of Socialist Democracy (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Qiao pointed out that they key to strengthening socialist
democracy and building a legal system lies in governing the
country in accordance with the Constitution and laws.
</P>
<P>
The Constitution stipulates that all power belongs to the
people, he said. Therefore, high attention should be paid to
respecting and guaranteeing people's political rights, mobilizing
people's initiative, and creating conditions for people to take
part in democratic elections, administration, supervision and
decision making.
</P>
<P>
The Constitution stipulates that the organ through which people
exercise state power is the National People's Congress and local
people's congresses at different levels, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
He called for persistence in and improvement of this
fundamental political system under the leadership of the Party, by
firmly protecting the rights of people's congress deputies
according to law, and giving full play to the functions of
people's congresses and their standing committees.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said the Party always emphasizes that no organization or
individual has the prerogative to override the Constitution and
the law, adding that all government departments should exercise
their power strictly in accordance with law, while leading cadres,
in particular, should familiarize themselves with the Constitution
and gain legal knowledge necessary for the performance of their
duties, and conscientiously do their work according to legal
provisions and proceedings.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that this year's legislative task remains heavy,
the chairman urged legislators to accelerate the pace of law
enactment and improve legislative quality, to establish the
framework of a legal system catering for a socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
With progress in reform, opening-up and modernization, he said,
more laws concerning a socialist market economy and promoting a
socialist democratic political system, and others, will be
enacted, for the establishment of a socialist legal system with
Chinese characteristics, he said.
</P>
<P>
In conformity with a principle set forth by Deng Xiaoping in
the early 1980s, he said, laws must be loyally and strictly
enforced, and any infringement upon laws by law enforcers, the
overriding of laws with administrative authorities, and perversion
of justice for personal gains, must be stopped.
</P>
<P>
He called for increased supervision over the work of
governments, courts and procuratorates, and over all personnel in
government departments elected or appointed by people's congresses
and their standing committees.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said the NPC Standing Committee is drafting a supervision
law according to the Constitution, to systemize and legalize
supervision work.
</P>
<P>
Finally, the chairman pointed out that the year of 1997 is a
very important one in the history of China's development.
</P>
<P>
He called on the legislators to carry work forward at the
behest of Deng Xiaoping, and guided by the theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and the basic line of the
Party, more closely unite around the Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core, to advance the great cause of socialist
modernization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial Hails Closing of NPC, CPPCC Sessions (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper, the
People's Daily, will publish an editorial tomorrow to hail the
closing of the annual sessions of the country's legislature and top
advisory body.
</P>
<P>
The fifth session of the Eighth National People's Congress
(NPC) and the fifth session of the Eighth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
have fulfilled their respective planned agendas and concluded
successfully, says the editorial, which is titled "To Accomplish
the Great Cause with One Heart and One Mind."
</P>
<P>
"This year's two sessions were convened soon after the death of
our beloved Comrade Deng Xiaoping, and both the NPC deputies and
CPPCC members turned their grief into strength and performed their
sacred duties in a spirit of being highly responsible to the
country and the nation, enabling the sessions to score great
achievements," the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
The fifth session of the Eighth NPC reviewed and approved
Premier Li Peng's report on the work of the government, the plan
for national economic and social development in 1997 and the 1997
central budget, the amended Criminal Law, the National Defense
Law, a decision on the quota allocation and election of deputies
to the Ninth NPC, a method for the election of deputies to the
Ninth NPC from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, a
decision on promoting Chongqing to a province-level municipality
directly under the authority of the central government, and a
number of other important documents, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
The fifth session of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee made
important contributions to the formulation of the above documents
by actively engaging in political consultation, democratic
supervision, and participation in and deliberation of state and
government affairs, and by making proposals through drawing on
collective wisdom and absorbing all useful ideas, it says.
</P>
<P>
The great achievements scored during the two sessions will play
an important role in facilitating socialist economic construction,
in developing democracy and a legal system, in national defense
construction, in the overall progress of all social undertakings,
as well as in ensuring a smooth return of Hong Kong, the editorial
notes.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the two sessions indicates that people of all
ethnic groups are determined to rally more closely round the CPC
Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core and are
confident of victoriously pushing forward the great cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated by
Comrade Deng Xiaoping," it says.
</P>
<P>
This year is the second year when China implements its Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and its outline of long-term objectives
for the year 2010. It is also a year when China will resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and the CPC will convene
its 15th national congress, it says.
</P>
<P>
"These are two big events in the development history of our
Party and our country," the editorial says, adding that a good job
must be done to ensure the success of the two events and calling
for a greater effort to score new successes in reform, opening up
and the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The tasks set forth in the government work report must be
earnestly carried out to ensure a sustained, rapid and healthy
development of the national economy, the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
It also says that the continuity, stability and necessary
flexibility of the macroeconomic policy should be maintained and
moderately tight fiscal and monetary policies should be continued,
so as to curb price rises.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be made to consolidate the status of
agriculture as the foundation of the national economy and to
accelerate reform, especially reform in state-owned enterprises,
the editorial says.
</P>
<P>
 It adds that equal importance should be attached to
material progress and to ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial Hails Closing of NPC, CPPCC Sessions (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial calls for the advancement of building a socialist
country with a sound legal system under the leadership of the
Party, by strengthening legislation and supervision of law
enforcement and by establishing a legal system that meets the
demands of a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
With the adoption of the amended Criminal Law, it says, crimes
will be cracked down upon, people protected, and national unity
and security, social order and the socialist system safeguarded.
</P>
<P>
And the Defense Law, also adopted at the current NPC session,
will be implemented to accelerate the pace of defense
modernization to guarantee a smooth progression of reform,
opening-up and socialist modernization, and long-term stability of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return to China is the common aspiration of the
whole nation, it points out, and preparations should be well made
in the last days of the transitional period to ensure Hong Kong's
return on time and its long-term stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
It says the policy of "peaceful reunification, and one country,
two systems" should be better publicized to promote national
reunification.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says: "The Chinese government and the Chinese
people have the determination and the ability to defend their
country's territorial integrity and national sovereignty, and
under no circumstances will they allow the separation of Taiwan
from the motherland. Any attempt to split the motherland is doomed
to fail."
</P>
<P>
The people's congress system is China's fundamental political
system, it says, and the multi-party cooperation and political
consultation system under the leadership of the CPC is its basic
political system.
</P>
<P>
This year is the last for the current terms of NPC and CPPCC
National Committee, the editorial says, calling on people's
congresses and CPPCC committees at all levels to better exercise
their power and perform their duties to prepare for Hong Kong's
return and the convocation of the 15th National Congress of the
CPC, and create good conditions for the next terms of NPC and
CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the Party Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at the core, the editorial says, Party members, especially
cadres at all levels, should hold higher the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, carry forward the good traditions of maintaining
close links with the masses and working hard, to strive for the
fulfillment of the country's grand trans-century goals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
