<HEADLINE> Founding of Chongqing Municipality Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The city of Chongqing has become
China's fourth municipality after Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin,
with approval today by the on-going annual session of the National
People's Congress (NPC), China's legislature.
</P>
<P>
The newly-established Chongqing Municipality will include the
original Chongqing City as well as Wanxian and Fuling cities and
Qianjiang Prefecture, according to a decision adopted by the Fifth
Session of the Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision, the State Council, China's cabinet,
will make corresponding readjustments to the organizational system
and divisions of the administrative areas under its jurisdiction
in line with the Chinese Constitution and relevant laws.
</P>
<P>
Today's decision gave birth to China's largest city with an
area of 82,000 sq km area and a combined population of 30.02
million in the original Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
With a history of more than 3,000 years, Chongqing was opened
up as a trade port in 1891 and officially became a city in 1929.
The city was a political and cultural center in soutwest China in
the early years following the founding of new China and, In 1954,
it was made a city directly under the jurisdiction of the Sichuan
Provincial Government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> A Strategic Decision for China's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- For some, it is conjecture
confirmed; for others, it is expectation fulfilled. For Chongqing,
it is another glorious page in its 3,000-year history.
</P>
<P>
With the adoption of a major resolution today by the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC) at the final plenary meeting of
its current session, Chongqing has become a centrally-administered
municipality, signaling, in the eyes of many people, an important
step forward in China's trans-century development strategy.
</P>
<P>
As the largest city and an economic center in the upper reaches
of the Yangtze River, Chongqing is expected to spearhead economic
development in China's central and western regions as well as in
the Yangtze River valley, a major component of the country's
development strategy for years before the end of this century and
the first two or three decades of the next.
</P>
<P>
Medium- and long-range plans adopted by the Fourth Session of
the Eighth NPC last year made it clear that the central government
will grant preferential policies for the underdeveloped central
and western regions to spur their economic development.
</P>
<P>
At the juncture of economically developed eastern China and the
resources-rich west, and as the leading industrial and commercial
city in southwest China, Chongqing is the key link between China's
east and west.
</P>
<P>
With its industrial, economic and scientific strength,
Chongqing has become the center of an economic cooperation area
covering 19 cities and prefectures in the three provinces of
Sichuan, Guizhou and Yunnan, with an area of 287,000 sq km, an
industrial and agricultural output value of 170 billion yuan, and
a population close to 200 million.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government initiated the strategy of developing the
Yangtze River valley at the beginning of the 1990s, aiming to
develop the valley into the largest inland industrial belt in the
world.
</P>
<P>
At what is called the "dragon head" of the valley is the
booming Pudong New Area of Shanghai. Chongqing, as the "dragon
tail" of the valley and with its new status, is expected to match
Pudong in development speed. Both, in turn, will contribute to
economic development of the whole country.
</P>
<P>
A special mission for the new municipality is to explore a new
development path for a metropolis galvanizing its surrounding
rural areas economically in the process of its own development.
</P>
<P>
With 24 million out of its 30 million people being rural
residents, and with three million of them living below the poverty
line, Chongqing will meet an unprecedent challenge. And its
success is crucial to the overall development of China with vast
rural regions and a big rural population.
</P>
<P>
For Chongqing, the most important task at the moment is to
relocate 1.07 million out of a total of 1.2 million people living
around the area where the Three Gorges project, China's biggest
ever water conservancy and hydropower project, is being
constructed.
</P>
<P>
And successful relocation will be Chongqing's greatest
contribution to this trans-century project, which is scheduled to
be completed by 2009.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing's Top-Position Claims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing City, which has become
China's fourth centrally-administered municipality today, has some
of the best and biggest in China's interior areas, the entire
country and the world. Following are some of them:
</P>
<P>
-- It covers an area of 82,000 square kilometers with a
population of 30.5 million, the biggest city in the world in terms
of population and land area;
</P>
<P>
-- Chongqing has 237.2 billion cubic meters of verified natural
gas reserves and 4.3 billion in annual output. Its Chuandong
Natural Gas Field with Chongqing as the center is China's largest
natural gas field;
</P>
<P>
-- As an automotive city in southwest China, Chongqing
produced 1.8 million motorcycles in 1996 to rank first in China;
</P>
<P>
-- With 49 defense industry factories employing some 200,000
people, Chongqing is China's largest production base for military
products;
</P>
<P>
-- The Wushan tourist site in the well-known Three Gorges
Scenic Zone was visited by more than one million people in 1996, a
single area visited by the greatest number of people in China;
</P>
<P>
-- Chongqing was approved by the State Council as the first
foreign trade port in interior areas in 1983 and is the first city
in the country to undertake comprehensive economic restructuring
in 1984. It is also among the first group of Chinese cities to go
for financial reform in 1987. The city claims the biggest foreign
trade volume in western China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
