<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing Party Secretary on Development Strategy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing will cherish the rare
opportunity of development that has resulted from its new status
as a centrally-administered municipality, and serve as the
"bellwether" for economic takeoff in central and western China.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Party Secretary Zhang Deling made this remark here
today, shortly after the National People's Congress decided to
establish Chongqing as a municipality directly under the central
government.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing municipality, the country's fourth after Beijing,
Tianjin and Shanghai, is now the most populous city across the
world, with 30 million people and an area of 82,000 square
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
"Chongqing will play a significant role in the construction of
the Three Gorges Project, and in economic development of the upper
reaches of the Yangtze River and central and western China," said
Zhang Deling, 57, a graduate of Qinghua University and a former
vice minister of machine building.
</P>
<P>
Among the one million people to be resettled to give way to the
Three Gorges Project, the world's largest water conservancy and
hydropower project, more than 80 percent are under the
jurisdiction of Chongqing municipality.
</P>
<P>
"The primary task for Chongqing is to relocate these people for
the Three Gorges Project," Zhang noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, with an expansion in area, Chongqing now
has a bigger poor population, which now stands at close to three
million, or one tenth of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
"It is a new and arduous task for Chongqing to help these
people shake off poverty, along with revitalizing local
industries, maintaining an ecological balance and controlling
pollution," he said, adding that the city has set new strategic
goals for its economic growth in view of the new situation.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chongqing would try to build in several years a
new group of industries in areas around the vast lake behind the
Three Gorges Dam to echo those in the Pudong New Area of Shanghai,
and bring about an integration and mutual prosperity of its urban
and rural economies by means of developing a network of modern
cities and towns of all sizes.
</P>
</TEXT>
