<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rich Resources to Lend Wing to Chongqing's Economic Takeoff (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chongqing's chemical and metal processing industries based on
local natural resources are well developed.
</P>
<P>
Vice mayor Li said, however, that the city's use of mineral
resources is still far from enough, citing the fact that the local
chemical industry only uses about 400 million cubic meters of
natural gas each year.
</P>
<P>
According to Chongqing's new development scheme, he said, a
chemical industry using local natural gas and salt reserves would
become one of the municipality's pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
"In the next several years, Chongqing will set up or expand a
dozen factories producing chemical materials and products, which
each year will consume an additional one billion cubic meters of
natural gas, and make profits of more than three billion yuan," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from underground mineral resources, Chongqing will also
attach importance to a comprehensive use of its water,
agricultural, and forest resources.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has hydropower reserves of nearly eight
million kilowatts, half of which can be exploited, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Three Gorges Reservoir with a length of 600 km,
which is to result from the Three Gorges Dam, will provide good
conditions to develop eco-agriculture, tourism, water
transportation, and aquaculture. A number of cities and towns are
expected to emerge around the huge man-made lake.
</P>
<P>
The vast countryside of Chongqing, especially the mountains and
hills of Fuling, Wanxian and Qianjiang, which have been put under
Chongqing's jurisdiction, produce a huge variety of agricultural
produce. The area, for example, leads the country in the output of
tung oil, raw lacquer and citrus fruit.
</P>
<P>
Qiu Wanxing, agricultural advisor to the Chongqing municipal
government, said: "At the initial stage of economic takeoff,
Chongqing should develop a processing industry for agricultural
products and by-products, and help farmers turn natural resources
into wealth. This might be the most realistic and quickest way for
Chongqing's urban and rural areas to achieve common prosperity."
</P>
</TEXT>
