<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan Envisions Greater Development after Chongqing's Departure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Establishment of the
centrally-administered Chongqing municipality, which used to be
part of Sichuan province, will benefit the development of both
Chongqing and Sichuan, a top Sichuan official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Xie Shijie, secretary of the provincial Party committee of
Sichuan, made the remark folowing a decision of the Eighth
National People's Congress to establish Chongqing as a
centrally-administered municipality.
</P>
<P>
Establishment of Chongqing municipality will promote social and
economic development in both Sichuan and Chongqing, and will be
conducive to a balanced economic development of both southwest
China and the entire country, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed support for the NPC decision on behalf of the
Sichuan provincial Party committee and the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Before Chongqing's departure, Sichuan was China's biggest
province with a population of 111 million, equal to those of
Britain and France combined, said Xie, adding it has been a
demanding job to run such a big province.
</P>
<P>
"In a long-term view and for the benefit of all," the Party
secretary noted, "the establishment of Chongqing municipality,
which includes the city proper and the two (prefectural level)
cities of Wanxian and Fuling and the prefecture of Qianjiang is a
welcome strategy."
</P>
<P>
After Chongqing has left its fold, Sichuan now has a population
of 83.57 million, ranking third in the nation.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of Chongqing municipality will enable Sichuan
to concentrate on development of the central area of the Sichuan
Basin, where the provincial capital of Chengdu is located, and to
play a better role in leading the economic growth of the entire
western China, said Xie.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, he added, it will benefit the development of
Wanxian, Fuling and Qianjiang. With their close proximity to
Chongqing, it is more convenient for Chongqing to administrate
these largely rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Finally, it will contribute to the Three Gorges Project, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The key to achieving the success of the project is the
relocation of residents around the Three Gorges area, he
explained, and 85 percent of people to be relocated live near
Chongqing and in Wanxian, Fuling and Qianjiang. And Chongqing can,
according to local conditions, adjust its industrial structure to
promote economic growth, thus better accomplishing the relocation
task.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sichuan will provide good conditions for
Chongqing, adding "we used to be one family, and we will be good
neighbors in future."
</P>
<P>
He said the separation of administrative powers does not mean a
severing of economic ties, and commodities exchanges between the
two will be even closer.
</P>
<P>
After the adjustment of administrative jurisdiction, Xie said,
Sichuan will also readjust its development strategy, by
consolidating its agriculture, transport, energy, education and
scientific research sectors, and strengthening its electronic and
information, machinery, building and building materials, beverage
and food, and travel industries as its industrial pillars.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that Chongqing as a centrally-administered
municipality will enjoy more policy support from the central
government, and expressed the belief that, combined with the
creativity of its people, Chongqing will fully display its
strength in three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
