<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Sowetan
</P>
<P>
-- South African President Nelson Mandela has appointed
special investigation and tribunal units to root out corruption
and graft in government departments countrywide, officials said
yesterday.
</P>
