<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Step to Maturity in China's Legal System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC) passed the new, amended Criminal
Law at its closing meeting in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Legal experts said the new Criminal Law, which will come into
effect on October 1 this year, has made a significant reform on
China's criminal legal framework and judicial system, and is
another indication that China's legal system has increasingly been
improved and the development of its legality is heading towards
maturity following the enactment of the new Criminal Procedure Law
in March, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The most distinct characteristic of the new Criminal Law is
that it has made as detailed, comprehensive and concrete
stipulations as possible on all kinds of criminal offences, so as
to protect the citizens' rights and interests in an all-round way,
ensure judicial fairness, and safeguard the smooth growth of a
socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
"Availability of laws on all occasions and judicial fairness
are basic symptoms of a country's matured legal system," one
legal expert noted.
</P>
<P>
Having gone through solicitation of views on an extensive scale
and, deliberations, additions and revisions at two NPC Standing
Committee sessions and the current NPC session, which was attended
by approximately 3,000 legislators, the new Criminal Law now has
452 articles, 260 more than the previous one.
</P>
<P>
"This law can ensure that no criminal escape punishment," said
Tao Xiping, vice-chairman of the Beijing Municipal People's
Congress Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new Criminal Law has improved the criminal
judicial proceeding, and laid a solid basis for handling criminal
cases in strict accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Binsheng, vice-chairman of the All-China Lawyers
Association, said that from the perspective of legal
professionals, the most impressive aspect of the new Criminal Law
is the further affirmation of the principles of "conviction and
penalty according to law," "equality for all before the law," and
"penalties commensurate with crimes."
</P>
<P>
"Just like the principle that 'a person should be deemed
innocent until proved guilty by courts' endorsed in the new
Criminal Procedure Law, the three principles constitute the
cornerstone in administering the country according to law, and has
great significance to preventing abuse of power by judicial
departments and safeguarding citizens' legitimate rights and
interests," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Rigid and specific stipulations on penalty reduction,
release-on-parole, and legitimate defence in the new Criminal Law
are also intended to guarantee judicial fairness, he added.
</P>
<P>
Gao Mingxuan, vice-president of the China Law Society and a
renowned expert on criminal laws, said that the new Criminal Law
is attributed to the prolonged and assiduous efforts of China and
the Chinese people in the building of a legal system.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of reform and opening up in late 1978, the
NPC, China's top legislature, has enacted more than 300 laws,
which almost cover all aspects of the country's political,
economic and social life.
</P>
<P>
The principle of judicial fairness has also been embodied in
administrative, economic, civil and other kinds of laws.
</P>
<P>
In this country with a long history of feudalism, civilians had
unprecedentedly been granted the right to sue the government with
the help of an Administrative Procedure Law, while the Law on
State Compensation had for the first time enabled citizens to
claim damages from the state.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, continuous efforts are being made to further improve
the existing legal system and judicial justice.
</P>
<P>
"After the amendments are made to the Criminal Law, the NPC and
its Standing Committee will undertake to amend the Marriage Law
and enact a Civil Code, and work to formulate a series of new
laws," said an official with the NPC Standing Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0216 </DOCNO>
