<HEADLINE> Sino-Japan Cooperation in Telecommunication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan opened a new
telecommunications joint venture in Shanghai Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai NTT Telecommunication Engineering Co., set up by
the Shanghai Posts and Telecommunications Administrative Bureau
and Nippon Telegraph &AMP; Telephone Corporation in Japan, will
provide consultation and technical support for Shanghai's
telecommunication digital mobile telephone network and other
networks.
</P>
<P>
The new venture will also serve firms in Shanghai and
surrounding areas by providing services to plan, design and
maintain inter-firm telecommunication networks.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, Shanghai has seen rapid
telecommunication development. The switchboard volume in the
municipality reached 4.5 million lines and the number of phone
subscribers reached 3.03 million in 1996, leading the country's
large cities. 
</P>
