<HEADLINE> America's Cup Damaged in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The America's Cup, a symbol
for the pride of New Zealand, was attacked today by a young man
with a sledge hammer at the Royal NZ Yacht Squadron Headquarters
in Auckland.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old attacker was arrested and charged with criminal
damage. He will appear in court on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
TV3 has received a letter which claims responsibility for the
attack, Radio New Zealand reported.
</P>
<P>
The letter is said to be from the Tino Rangatiratanga
Liberation Front campaigning for Maori sovereignty and threatens
action against the government.
</P>
<P>
It said the first act of defiance will be the destruction of
the national monument of great significance and its objective is
the establishment of an independent Maori state.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Jim Bolger said he is disgusted by the attack on
the America's Cup, which was taken home in 1995 by the victorious
yacht Endeavour.  
</P>
