<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- New technology and talented
personnel from abroad boosted economic development in eastern
China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has invited 2,500 foreign experts in
the fields of education, technology, and management and sent
around 2,000 local people overseas for professional training in
1996, representing a 22 percent and 34 percent rise respectively
from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Specialists from abroad have brought in 38 high-tech projects
and 36 business ventures involving a total investment of 200
million US dollars and 1.7 billion yuan (205 million US dollars)
in added output value.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector invited 80 overseas specialists to
offer guidance in vegetable growing and to inspect quality
control, which improved the product quality and raised output.
</P>
<P>
The Shandong Provincial Academy of Agriculture has used
imported seed strains to double the wheat output.
</P>
<P>
With the help of overseas technicians, 14 breweries from
various parts of Shandong have improved beer-making technology to
make their products come up to general standards. 
