<HEADLINE> Second Prototype of New Trainer Plane Crashed in Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A second prototype of the
newly-designed Seagull trainer aircraft crashed Wednesday in the
Batajnica military airport, near Belgrade, during a trial fight,
killing the test pilot.
</P>
<P>
The Seagull aircraft designed and made by the UTVA (Fabrika
Aviona) plane plant was expected to replace the UTVA-75 and
Seagull-2. It had two breakdowns during an earlier test fight.
</P>
<P>
A first prototype of the Seagull crashed due to technical
stoppage during a trial fight in 1985.
</P>
<P>
The plane's maximum speed reaches 340 kilometers per hour in
level flight, with a ceiling height of 5,200 meters and a
deadweight capacity of 1.65 tons.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash is under investigation and mass
production of the Seagull plane become questionable. 
</P>
