<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, Mozambique Seek Ways to Boost Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A two-day Eighth Joint Commission
between Zimbabwe and Mozambique started here yesterday to seek
ways to remove barriers which hinder increased bilateral trade.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the officials from both countries will resolve
such problems arising from tariffs, user fees, visa requirements
and other administrative issues.
</P>
<P>
Officially opening the session, Zimbabwean Foreign Minister
Stan Mudenge said the meeting also afforded both sides an
opportunity to review bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"We must ensure that more and more barriers are removed if
trade is to be further increased," he said.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries would increase tremendously if
the two countries sign a bilateral preferential trade agreement,
he said. 
</P>
