<HEADLINE> Car Rental Industry Develops In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Although Shanghai's car rental
industry is only four years old, China's largest city now has nine
car renting companies operational, with over 800 cars available.
</P>
<P>
There are over 20 types of cars for rent, ranging from luxury
sedans, Cadillac, BMW, and Mercedes, to compacts like the Santana.
</P>
<P>
The main clients of Shanghai's car rental market are overseas
businessmen, overseas-invested companies, and agencies of other
cities.
</P>
<P>
A car rental executive said that two new trends were observed
in 1996: more people rent cars during holidays, and, institutions
make long term car rentals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
