<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Dock Passes Muster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The 300,000-ton dock in Dalian, a
coastal city in northeast China's Liaoning Province, just passed
state assessment.
</P>
<P>
The "No. 1 China Dock" is 365 meters long, 80 meters wide, and
12.7 meters deep. It is capable of building and repairing large
vessels and offshore drilling platforms. A 900-ton jack has Asia's
largest span.
</P>
<P>
The dock was designed by the China State Shipbuilding
Corporation. Construction work started in March of 1989.
</P>
<P>
Since the first ship was built at the dock in January of 1995,
the dock has accommodated a dozen ships, demonstrating its high
quality and efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
