weapons from army depots and started fighting the
military. Several cities in southern Albania are in the hands of
rebels who are now threatening to move onto the capital.
</P>
<P>
Albanian President Sali Berisha and all political parties have
allegedly called on the Western European Union to provide military
assistance to Tirana to restore order in the country which is
verging on civil war. 
