<HEADLINE> Foreign Loans Boost Guangxi's Transportation Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
has used 150 million US dollars of foreign loans to boost its
transportation infrastructure, turning the region into an emerging
economy in south China.
</P>
<P>
The region injected a World Bank loan of about 80 million US
dollars into the second-phase project of a navigation hub on the
Xijiang River. Most of the work has been completed.
</P>
<P>
The construction of an expressway between Qinzhou and
Fangchenggang now is well underway, with a loan of 52 million US
dollars from the Asian Development Bank. The roadway will be
operational in the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Government loans from the Republic of Korea and the
Netherlands, which amount to 10 million U.S. dollars and 13
million U.S. dollars, respectively, were poured into the auxiliary
projects for two ports in Qinzhou and Beihai.  
