<HEADLINE> New Season of China's Soccer League Begins on Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 season of China's
professional soccer league will finally kickoff in six cities
around the country on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It has been a long and anxiou waiting for the Chinese soccer
fans to get into the holiday atmosphere the league brings to their
daily life since the ending of the previous season which saw
Dalian Wanda taking the title for the second time in three years.
</P>
<P>
Now, after a hard and strict winter training session in
Kunming, Yunnan Province, each of the 12 teams participating in
this year's league will try the best to prove to the fans that it
deserves their support.
</P>
<P>
Among the 12 teams, Vanguard Huandao and Qingdao Hainiu were
promoted from the second division after taking the top two places
last season.
</P>
<P>
Others includes reigning champions Dalian Wanda, runners-up
Shanghai Shenhua, Football Association Cup titlists Beijing
Guo'an, the August First (Army's team), Jinan Taishan, Yanbian
Aodong, Tianjin Lifei, Guangzhou Apollo, Guangdong Hongyuan and
Sichuan Quanxing.
</P>
<P>
After a series of signings and transfers, the new season will
be hard to predict from the very start.
</P>
<P>
Vanguard Huandao, titlists of the second division last season,
will play at home their first ever professional league match
against Dalian Wanda, two-time titlists of China's top soccer
league.
</P>
<P>
Due to suspensions, injuries and modest signings compared with
last season, Dalian Wanda can hardly field in the match against
the Vanguards a line-up as strong as last season.
</P>
<P>
Though the defending champions have seven Chinese
internationals in the team, their rivals are not at all modest
with eight former Chinese internationals plus German coach Klaus
Schlappner, former head coach of Chinese national squad.
</P>
<P>
Unlike most of the Chinese coaches, the out-spoken Schlappner
earned a name of aggressiveness during his coaching of the Chinese
national team.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese fans are anxious to know if Schlappner can lead his
team to stop Dalian Wanda's 34-match unbeaten record in the
league. If the German coach succeeds, then the new season will be
more interesting and exciting to the fans.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches on Sunday, last year's runners-up Shanghai
Shenhua will take on Yanbian Aodong.
</P>
<P>
The two teams both signed a new head coach from abroad with
Shanghai Shenhua now has a Bulgarian while the Yanbian team gets a
South Korean coach.
</P>
<P>
It is hard to predict what kind of match the two teams will
play in the first round. But it is clear that with the
line-up almost unchanged, the host team Shanghai Shenhua boost a
great chance of winning the season-opening match.
</P>
<P>
The other actings on Sunday will see Beijing play Sichuan
Quanxing at home, Tianjin Lifei take on the August First, Jinan
Taishan play Qingdao Hainiu, the other team from Shandong Province
and Guangzhou Apollo play Guangdong Hongyuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
