<HEADLINE> Series of Books on Tibetan Buddhism Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- A series of books on Tibetan
Buddhism are being published by the Qinghai People's Publishing
House.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the Tibet Autonomous Region, Qinghai Province in
northwest China is one of the country's territories which are home
to the Tibetan community.
</P>
<P>
Five books of the "Cultural Phenomena of Tibetan Buddhism
Series" are now available, and another seven books are expected to
reach readers soon.
</P>
<P>
The books, containing a total of 1.8 million Chinese
characters, were compiled by a team of middle-aged and young
Tibetan scholars after years of work.
</P>
<P>
They expound on a number of topics concerning Tibetan Buddhism,
such as its formation and development, philosophical significance,
Tantric Sect, or doctrine, arts, funeral customs, mythology, and
the life of monks.
</P>
<P>
Many scholars of Tibetology regard the books as an encyclopedia
of Tibetan Buddhism which, after more than 1,300 years of
development, has become one of the most popular and
long-established religions in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
