<HEADLINE> Dalian Builds Resort Complex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Construction has just begun on a
resort complex in Dalian, a coastal city in northeast China's
Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The Jinshitan, or "Golden Stone Beach," vacation getaway will
have tourist facilities such as villas, apartment buildings,
hotels, and a recreation center, covering a total area of 67,000
square meters.
</P>
<P>
The resort will be built around Dalian's three clubs that each
have international standards -- a golf club, a pleasure-boat club,
and a hunt club -- to form one large tourism zone. Jinshitan will
also set up the biggest production base for fresh flowers in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
A company from the Philippines invested 50 million US dollars
for the resort complex. The project was approved by the Chinese
government in 1992, sources say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
