<HEADLINE> Beijing to Add 230,000 Mobile Phones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital city will add
230,000 mobile phone subscriptions this year, bringing the total
to 500,000, according to the Ministry of Posts and
Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Beijing had 285,000 mobile phone users by the end of 1996,
nearly 130,000 of which were added last year. And the number of
digital mobile phone users added last year reached nearly 100,000.
</P>
