<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Worried About Albanian Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav federal government
today expressed deep concern over the serious situation in
Albania, saying that the chaos there would "make the regional
situation complicated".
</P>
<P>
A government communique said Yugoslavia would adopt the policy
of non-interference towards Albania's tense situation, which was
the country's internal affair.
</P>
<P>
It said the Yugoslav government hoped that the crisis in
Albania would be solved by peaceful and political means.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme Defense Council of Yugoslavia decided today to
heighten the level of military alert and continue completely
sealing its borders with Albania.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia is the second of Albania's neigbors to close its
border, following Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The council said the Yugoslav army and the interior ministry
troops have so far controlled the situation on the borders and
have taken measures to ensure the security of the republic.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav federal government is particularly concerned about
the situation in Albania because 90 percent of the population in
the southern Serbian province of Kosovo are Albanians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
