<HEADLINE> Cuba Says Niger FM Visit "Productive" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban Foreign Ministry said
today that the five-day visit to Cuba of Niger Foreign Minister
Ibrahim Assane Mayaki had been "very productive and successful."
</P>
<P>
Cuba and Niger today signed a series of agreements on bilateral
cooperation in commerce, health, the sugar industry and sports,
said Marianela Ferriol, acting spokesman for the Cuban Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The Niger foreign minister also expressed interest in Niger
participation in an international youth festival to be held in
Cuba.
</P>
<P>
He and Victoria Velazquez, the first secretary of Cuban Youth,
exchanged views on the preparations for the 14th World Youth and
Students Festival, which will be held from July 28 to August 5 in
Cuba, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
