<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four US Basketball Players Arrested in Attack on Policeman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Five Americans, including four
professional basketball players, have been arrested in Nicosia for
allegedly attacking an off-duty Cypriot policeman, leaving him in
a coma, police said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, who were not identified, allegedly attacked riot
squad policeman Christodoulos Christodoulou early Thursday at a
restaurant in a Nicosia suburb, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said a fight broke out after Christodoulou asked one of
the five Americans to stop bothering his date. A number of other
customers in the restaurant became involved in the brawl and
police were called to the scene.
</P>
<P>
Christodoulou, 25, allegedly suffered a fractured skull and was
in critical condition in Nicosia General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the Americans, aged between 25 and 27, were
arrested and remanded in custody for five days by a Nicosia
district court on charges of causing grievous bodily harm.
</P>
<P>
Police said four of the Americans in custody play basketball
for local first division teams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
