<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba to Restore Historical Trinidad City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has set up an office to
oversee the renovation of the historical city of Trinidad in
central Cuba, known for its rich colonial architecture.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban Council of Ministers vested the Trinidad Curatorship
Office with cultural and juridical authority in preserving the
cultural, architectural and spiritual treasures of the city, which
was designated a Cultural Heritage City by the United Nations
Organization for Education, Science, and Culture (UNESCO) in 1988.
</P>
<P>
The office will plan and carry out restoration projects and
raise funds for them.
</P>
<P>
Companies in Trinidad are being asked to donate three percent
of their profits to help fund the city's preservation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
