<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Presidium of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress (NPC) decided at its third meeting Thursday to
put several draft laws and resolutions to a vote at the last
plenum of the session due today.
</P>
<P>
-- The UN General Assembly, in its first plenary meeting since
January, paid tribute to the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The NPC deputies and members of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee
pinned high hopes on the upcoming 15th Congress of Communist Party
of China to be held during the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
-- Louis Gerstner Jr., chairman of the IBM corporation of the
United States, said during talks with Chinese President Jiang
Zemin Thursday that his company will play a greater role in
China's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The United States should play a positive role in Hong Kong's
smooth transition and long-term prosperity and stability, said
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Cui Tiankai Thursday.
</P>
<P>
-- The on-going fifth session of the Eighth NPC received 700
new motions from deputies by March 7.
</P>
<P>
The motions mainly concern the socialist market mechanism,
reform of state-owned enterprises, agriculture, social security
system, science, education and legislation.
</P>
<P>
-- China's accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO) has
made some major progress recently, but there are still many
obstacles that remain to be overcome, said a statement from the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Thursday.
</P>
