<HEADLINE> Steels Wins fifth Stage at Paris-Nice Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Belgium's Tom Steels notched up his
third stage victory at the Paris-Nice cycling race when he
sprinted home to win the fifth stage on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Steels just finished ahead of Italy's Mario Cipollini and
France's world number one Laurent Jalabert, who retained his
leader's white jersey in this 198km stage from Cournon d'Auvergne
to Venissieux.
</P>
<P>
France's Jean-Jacques Henry took fourth place ahead of fellow
countryman Christophe Capelle and Italy's Fabio Baldato.
</P>
<P>
The stage saw a 94km lone breakaway by Thierry Gouvenou, but,
after good work from Steels teammates, he was swallowed up 15km
from the finish.
</P>
<P>
France's Christophe Moreau made a break coming up to the final
kilometre but faded to the 10th spot.
</P>
<P>
Steels has had an incredible race so far as he also won the two
mass sprint finishes on Monday and Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
