<HEADLINE> Ericsson to Expand Cellular Phone Production in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 14 (Xinhua) -- Ericsson, the leading Swedish
mobile telecom supplier, has launched an assembly line here to
manufacture cellular phones on a large scale, the latest issue of
People's Posts and Telecommunications has reported.
</P>
<P>
Installed in Beijing Ericsson Mobile Telecom Co. (BMC), an
Ericsson joint venture here, the CKD production line involves an
investment of more than four million US dollars, and boasts a yearly
producing capacity of 300,000 handsets.
</P>
<P>
The principle product of the line will be the new GH398 mobile
phone.
</P>
<P>
So far, the annual sales of BMC have reached 1.4 billion
yuan-worth, including 260,000 mobile phones sold on the domestic
market. The mobile phone sales are expected to exceed one million
handsets this year.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson will also establish a research and development
institute here this year, in a move to speed up the joint
venture's effort to localize, the paper said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
