<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 284 AIDS Cases Registered in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 284 AIDS cases have
been registered in Nicaragua since the disease was first reported
in 1987, the Health Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said Nicaragua continues to have the lowest rate
of AIDS cases among Central American countries, but the country
cannot rest on its laurels and needs to take measures to prevent
the disease spreading.
</P>
<P>
Honduras is the Central American country worst affected, with
6,000-8,000 terminal phase patients, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
El Salvador is second with 1,600 AIDS cases, followed by
Guatemala with 1,300, Panama 1,186, and Costa Rica 1,012.
</P>
<P>
The AIDS problem will be discussed by Central American
parliamentarians at a meeting here on March 17-18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
