<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania to Maintain Strategic Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Senate Chairman Petre
Roman said here on Thursday that Romania sees relations with China
as a key plank in its foreign policy strategy, in spite of the
international changes.
</P>
<P>
"I think Romania should establish and develop permanent
strategic relations with China," Roman said during a meeting with
China's new ambassador to Romania Liu Guchang.
</P>
<P>
Roman, who visited China in 1995, said China's reforms had left
a great impression on him. He said Romania will further develop
and extend exchanges and cooperation with China, especially in the
fields of the economy and trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
