<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0317 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Industrial Park Attracting More Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, March 14 (Xinhua) -- An increase in investment has
begun to appear in the Suzhou Industrial Park, a Sino-Singaporean
venture in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The park had 40 million US dollars in investment from abroad in
the first two months of the year, while 92 Chinese firms moved
there, bringing in 300 million yuan in investment.
</P>
<P>
The park approved 10 new overseas-funded firms in precision
machinery and electronics in the first two months.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen from more than 20 countries have come to Suzhou to
get a closer look in person, and the industrial park has signed
2.6 billion US dollars in contracts since it was built in May 1994.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-eight firms have gone operational, and by the end of
this year, the first phase of development of eight-sq-km will be
completed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
