<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China To Speed Up Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 14 (Xinhua) -- China's Northwest has turned vast
tracts of barren land into agricultural production bases, becoming
a major contributor to the country's grain production in the
process.
</P>
<P>
The Northwest includes the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, and Gansu, Qinghai, and Shaanxi
provinces. Grain output there was a record 32 billion kilograms in
1996, and it had the fastest increase in grain production in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Water is the major factor in agricultural development in
northwest China because of the dry climate. Obviously, water
conservation is always given top priority.
</P>
<P>
The area has spent about 10 billion yuan on irrigation works
over the past five years. Xinjiang and Shaanxi will put another
26.5 billion yuan into improving water facilities by the end of
the century.
</P>
<P>
Key water diversion or storage projects in the Northwest are
changing the imbalance in water resources, and will ensure
sustained agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
Water-saving irrigation methods such as drip irrigation are
being widely used in the Northwest. Xinjiang has put 300 million
yuan into building better canals, and Gansu, Shaanxi and Ningxia
initiated a rainfall irrigation method and built storage
facilities to catch rainwater.
</P>
<P>
Land improvement projects are tied to water conservation. More
than 330,000 ha of medium- to low-yield farmland are being
upgraded annually in the Northwest. The five regions and provinces
began to open up 13.3 million ha of arable wasteland in a regional
cooperative venture.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture has become the pillar industry in the Northwest and
is playing an increasingly important part in promoting sound
economic development in China. Xinjiang is now the country's
largest cotton production base and Shaanxi ranks second in apple
output. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970314.0322 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-14 </DATE_TIME>
