<HEADLINE> Albright Meets Polish FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright today met visiting Polish Foreign Minister
Dariusz Rosati, assuring that there will be no concessions to
Moscow on the terms of NATO membership of the applicants.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters before the meeting, Albright noted that
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization will make no concessions in
talks on a NATO-Russian charter to Moscow on the terms of the
entrance of the East and Central European countries.
</P>
<P>
"There are going to not be any second class citizens in an
enlarged NATO, " said she.
</P>
<P>
She affirmed that "it is very wrong" to characterize the
NATO-Russia discussions as concessions.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton and Russian President Boris Yeltsin
are due to meet in Helsinki next week, focusing on the expansion
of the alliance.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss a NATO-Russia charter for better
relations between Moscow and the alliance.
</P>
<P>
The East and Central European countries fear that the U.S. will
make concessions to Russia on the terms of theri membership in
NATO.
</P>
<P>
Albright said that the charter will serve the interests of
every country in Europe.  
</P>
