<HEADLINE> Bank of China Expands International Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Bank of China International (UK)
Ltd began trading here today after it had obtained all necessary
regulatory consents.
</P>
<P>
The merchant bank, a subsidiary of Bank of China International
Holdings Ltd which was set up in London two months ago, will offer
a wide range of banking services to European investors wishing to
invest in China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It will also trade debt and equity issued by Chinese borrowers,
structure finance for projects and exports, and corporate finance
and advisory services for foreign companies setting up in China
and Chinese companies seeking strategic partners, according to C.
G. Wu, chairman of the bank.
</P>
<P>
To celebrate the opening of the two newly-established merchant
banks, President of the Bank of China Wang Xuebing presided over a
grand ceremony here this evening, which was attended by
representatives from several hundred financial institutions
including Governor of the Bank of England Eddie George,
Vice-governor of the People's Bank of China Chen Yuan and Chairman
of the Hong Kong Monetary Authority Joseph Ren.
</P>
<P>
Brian Woolley, a former capital market executive of Citybank,
was appointed managing director of Bank of China International
(UK) Ltd. 
</P>
