<HEADLINE> European Shares Down on US Economic Data </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 13 (Xinhua) -- All the three major stock markets
in Europe had a poor day and ended lower Thursday, with Frankfurt
suffering the heaviest losses, undermined by new US economic data
which raised fresh fears of higher US interest rates.
</P>
<P>
British shares in London closed near its day's lows after a
weak Wall Street opening added to the gloom on the market, with
the FTSE 100 index 24.8 points lower at 4,397.7, breaching the
important 4,400-point level.
</P>
<P>
Renewed caution on medium-term inflation prospects from Bank of
England governor Eddie George had made the index in negative
territory all day.
</P>
<P>
On the Frankfurt market, the German DAX-30 index ended the
session sharply weaker, down 65.59 points at 3,349.81, but off its
low of 3,338.53.
</P>
<P>
A wave of profit-taking, the weaker dollar and lower German
debt prices hit share prices, but experts said consolidation was
healthy for the market after about a 20 percent gain in the last
10 weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse also finished lower as profit takers continued
to move in after the market's earlier record performances, with
the CAC-40 index down 9.6 points at 2,632.1.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index of leading British shares ended 24.8
points weaker at 4,397.7. In Frankfurt, the DAX-30 index closed
down 65.59 points at 3,349.81. The Paris CAC-40 index finished 9.6
points lower at 2,632.1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
