<HEADLINE> German Donor Trains 6,000 Farmers in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 13 (Xinhua)-- Over 6,000 local
small-scale Tanzanian farmers have received training from Hanns
Seidel Foundation, a German institute for international
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Resident Representative of the institute Klaus Sollfrank told
reporters here today that it cost the institute 5.4 billion
Tanzania Shillings (about nine million US Dollars) in the past
nine years to train these farmers.
</P>
<P>
He said the institute puts great emphasis on the agricultural
sector and win a lot of successes in the Kilimanjaro, Arusha,
Tanga, Morogoro, Mbeya and Mwanza regions in the eastern African
country.
</P>
<P>
Sollfrank said the training program involved farmers engaged
in maize growing and dairy cattle raising. enditem


